The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and hearth. Coffer the chimney, repair the damaged plaster and smooth it out. Build a custom closet.
You start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The messy stage is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the vent; all dried up :(
Ready for plastering next week
Happy with the little nook on the side.
Inserting the new closet here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a lovely little air vent so that the chimney doesn't take in the humidity.
The chimney sweep took care of installing the hat and the rain hat. That should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there.
The plasterer is finished. We are installing the floor tomorrow.
The foam underlay is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a roll of toilet paper as an attachment for the vacuum.
Some of the floorboards are sorted and ready to be laid. We're just taking a tea break.
Well, progress was slow today due to extremely delicate cuts around door posts to achieve a smooth transition to the hallway (which is also being laid). @user45 on Twitter cursed me out.
Finished, but on the joints! The cherry on top: the impossible-to-drink instructions to assemble the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
There are still the baseboards to do in the hallway, all of them. The decorator comes in a month, so meanwhile, at home, it's high-end plaster without finish.
This evening's DIY session is to remove the lower sections of the door posts at the table saw or hand saw where you want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The cork subfloor in the hallway is also laid.
We finished the flooring in the hallway yesterday. Then at 5am this morning, we headed to Heathrow to collect Chose 1, followed by a siesta and the final stretch to finish the hallway; baseboards were installed. We'll take care of sealing when the adhesive has set.
